# Plan: Convert Next.js Frontend to Vite + React SPA

## Context

The `frontend/` directory is currently a **Next.js 16 App Router** project, but the project specs (`context/file-structure.md`, `context/frontend-roadmap.md`, `context/ui-context.md`) define it as a **Vite + React SPA** with React Router 6. The Next.js app is actually already an SPA in disguise â€” it uses a single `page.tsx` with a custom `RouterContext` for client-side routing, zero server components, zero server-side data fetching, and zero file-based routing. The only Next.js-specific dependencies actually used in component code are `next-themes` (3 files) and `next/font/google` (1 file, layout.tsx). Everything else (shadcn/ui components, contexts, hooks, lib, mock data) is framework-agnostic.

**User constraints:** No Prisma â€” use raw PostgreSQL instead. Keep everything else per context specs.

---

