## Step 2: Scaffold Vite + React 19 + TypeScript

Create fresh Vite project files:

- **`package.json`** â€” New deps keeping the same packages the Next.js app actually uses (Radix UI, CVA, clsx, tailwind-merge, cmdk, date-fns, embla-carousel-react, framer-motion, lucide-react, react-day-picker, react-hook-form, react-markdown, react-resizable-panels, react-syntax-highlighter, recharts, sonner, vaul, zod, zustand, @dnd-kit/*, @tanstack/react-query, @tanstack/react-table, input-otp, @hookform/resolvers, @mdxeditor/editor). Remove: `next`, `next-auth`, `next-intl`, `next-themes`, `prisma`, `@prisma/client`, `sharp`, `bun-types`, `eslint-config-next`, `@tailwindcss/postcss`, `z-ai-web-dev-sdk`, `@reactuses/core`. Add: `vite`, `@vitejs/plugin-react`, `react-router-dom`, `msw` (dev), `vitest`, `@testing-library/react`, `@testing-library/jest-dom`, `jsdom` (dev), `prettier`, `prettier-plugin-tailwindcss` (dev). Scripts: `dev`, `build`, `preview`, `lint`, `test`, `typecheck`.
- **`vite.config.ts`** â€” `@vitejs/plugin-react`, path alias `@` â†’ `./src`, proxy `/api` â†’ `http://localhost:8080`.
- **`tsconfig.json`** â€” Remove `next` plugin, keep `@/*` path alias, target ES2022.
- **`tsconfig.app.json`** â€” Vite-style app config.
- **`tsconfig.node.json`** â€” Vite-style node config for vite.config.ts.
- **`postcss.config.js`** â€” `@tailwindcss/postcss` + `tailwindcss-animate`.
- **`tailwind.config.ts`** â€” Same content as current (v3-style config that's inert under v4, kept for shadcn CLI compatibility).
- **`eslint.config.js`** â€” Replace Next.js ESLint config with Vite-friendly flat config.
- **`.prettierrc`** â€” With `prettier-plugin-tailwindcss`.
- **`index.html`** â€” Vite entry HTML at project root (not in public/).
- **`public/logo.svg`** â€” Keep existing.
- **`public/robots.txt`** â€” Keep existing.
- **`public/mockServiceWorker.js`** â€” Generate via `npx msw init`.

