## Step 3: Create Vite entry points

- **`src/main.tsx`** â€” Mount `<App />` into `#root`, import `./index.css`.
- **`src/index.css`** â€” Move content from `src/app/globals.css` (Tailwind v4 imports, CSS variables, custom animations). Remove `@import "tw-animate-css"` if incompatible, replace with direct Tailwind animate utilities.
- **`src/App.tsx`** â€” React Router setup:
  ```
  <ThemeProvider> (from src/contexts/theme-context.tsx â€” new, replaces next-themes)
  <AuthProvider>
    <RouterProvider> (from react-router-dom BrowserRouter)
      <Routes>
        {/* Public layout routes */}
        <Route element={<PublicLayout />}>
          <Route path="/" element={<LandingPage />} />
          <Route path="/features" element={<FeaturesPage />} />
          ...
        </Route>
        {/* Auth routes (centered card, no layout) */}
        <Route path="/login" element={<LoginPage />} />
        ...
        {/* Protected routes */}
        <Route element={<ProtectedRoute />}>
          <Route element={<AppShell />}>
            <Route path="/student/dashboard" element={<StudentDashboard />} />
            ...
          </Route>
        </Route>
      </Routes>
    </RouterProvider>
  </AuthProvider>
  </ThemeProvider>
  ```
- **`src/vite-env.d.ts`** â€” Vite client types reference.

---

## Step 4: Create theme context (replaces next-themes)

- **`src/contexts/theme-context.tsx`** â€” Simple React context with `theme`, `setTheme`, `resolvedTheme`. Reads from `localStorage`, applies `.dark` class to `<html>`. Matches `next-themes` API shape so the 3 consuming components need minimal changes.

---

## Step 5: Convert routing (RouterContext â†’ React Router)

- **Delete** `src/contexts/router-context.tsx` (replaced by react-router-dom).
- **Update `src/contexts/auth-context.tsx`** â€” Remove `'use client'` directive. Keep everything else (it's pure React).
- **Update `src/types/index.ts`** (new file) â€” Move `AppRoute` type from `src/lib/api/types.ts`, keep as a union type for reference but routes are now actual URL paths.
- **Update all navigation calls** across every component:
  - `navigate('landing')` â†’ `navigate('/')`  (using `useNavigate()` from react-router-dom)
  - `navigate('login')` â†’ `navigate('/login')`
  - `navigate('student/dashboard')` â†’ `navigate('/student/dashboard')`
  - `currentRoute === 'landing'` â†’ `useLocation().pathname === '/'`
  - `goBack()` â†’ `navigate(-1)`
- **Update `src/components/layouts/public-layout.tsx`** â€” Replace `useRouter()` from custom context with `useNavigate()` + `useLocation()` from react-router-dom. Replace `next-themes` import with new theme context.
- **Update `src/components/layouts/app-shell.tsx`** â€” Same routing conversion.
- **Update `src/components/shared/theme-toggle.tsx`** â€” Replace `next-themes` with new theme context.
- **Update `src/components/ui/sonner.tsx`** â€” Replace `next-themes` with new theme context.
- **Update `src/app/page.tsx` logic â†’ `src/App.tsx`** â€” The `RouteContent` component's role-based guards move into a `<ProtectedRoute>` component.

